  "abstract": "Two entomopathogenic nematodes, Steinernema sp and\r\nHetero rhabditis, are important biocontrol agents for the\r\nmanagement of insect pests because of their wide host\r\nrange and high virulence (Poinar 1979). Surveys were\r\nconducted at ICRISAT Center between June and December\r\n1991 for steinernematid and heterorhabditid nematodes.\r\nSoil samples were collected from 110 sites in five\r\nVertisol and six Alfisol fields...",
